What you need to know:

Rachier believes the new signings have what it takes to steer the team to success next seasonThe record KPL champions Monday closed their transfer business after roping in 18-year-old striker Dickson Raila to reinforce its already crowded attackRaila will however fight for a starting berth with his fellow teen Benson Omala, Nichoals Kipkirui, youthful Clinton Okoth and Burundian forward Jules Ulimwengu